definition: to fall/to collapse/to lie horizontally/to overthrow/to fail/to go bankrupt/to change (trains or buses)/to move around/to resell at a profit

sentences.english: Some waters only allow single non barbed hooks.
sentences.chinese: 有些水域僅可使用無倒鉤的單鉤。

sentences.english: The striker does a fantastic bicycle kick and the ball touches the post and deflects into the net.
sentences.chinese: 前鋒做了一次精采用的倒鉤，球碰到立柱，折射入網。

sentences.english: Push the hose on and over all barbs and up to the wrench flats .
sentences.chinese: 將軟管推到所有倒鉤上，直到接頭上搭板手的平面處。

sentences.english: Slide the clamp up and center over the largest barb.
sentences.chinese: 將夾子滑上並將最大的倒鉤處於中心位置。

sentences.english: The Eskimo barbed the arrows with pointed fish bones.
sentences.chinese: 愛斯基摩人用尖魚刺作箭的倒鉤。

sentences.english: And even the opposition newspapers have given the president a temporary reprieve from their barbs.
sentences.chinese: 即使是反對派報紙給主席從他們的倒鉤暫時緩刑。

sentences.english: Policymakers traded barbs about whose actions harmed the world economy most.
sentences.chinese: 政策制定者交易有關的行爲損害了世界經濟最倒鉤。
